H. H. MOTTER, Collector of Internal Revenue for the District of Kansas, v. MENTHOLATUM COMPANY. No. 1104. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. June 11, 1934. L. E. Wyman, Asst. U. S. Atty., of Topeka, Kan., for appellant. Poulston, Siefkin, Foulston & Morris, of Wichita, Kan., for appellee.'

Before LEWIS, McDERMOTT, and BRATTON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed on motion of appellant.
